One bright sunny night, the APED turtles were shimmying down a particularly long bin pipe, when Fedox spotted a minion of the North Wind prying open orange violins with a jelly crowbar, presumably to reach the rich deposits of babbironium that, as you probably know, is found mostly in orange - and to a lesser extent, purple - violins. Searching for babbironium without a guinea pig is very illegal, and Fedox couldn&#39;t smell a guinea pig for miles around, so he fluffed his spines and danced angrily to the minion.
The minion was a small, pale-veridian gust of north-easterly wind, slightly squally, but without a bread hat. The normal custom for North Windian minions, when confronted by a law-enforcement officer, is to bow until their nose is level with the height of their guinea pig when it&#39;s standing on it&#39;s hind legs and hopping in time with the theme tune to Mork And Mindy. However, this minion didn&#39;t have a guinea pig, nor a nose, so Fedox and Teycanwyn began the normal procedure for breech of protocol.
&quot;Here, hold this.&quot; Fedox handed his partner a slapstick, a long, thin piece of a green tee-shirt spat on by low-flying nuns, and unfurled a tell-scroll from his pouch. &quot;State your name,&quot; he said to the minion.
&quot;Don&#39;t got one,&quot; the squall replied huffily.
&quot;Right, Doan Gotwon, you are in breech...&quot;
&quot;Nah, nah, nah, I mean, I don&#39;t got a name.&quot;
&quot;What the garf do you mean you don&#39;t have a name?! How the garf can you not have a name?!&quot;
The squall shrugged. &quot;Dunno. Just don&#39;t got one.&quot;
Fedox rolled his eyes. &quot;Right. Fine. Put a gust of wind here.&quot; He pointed to a spot on the tell-scroll.
&quot;D&#39; I &#39;ave to?&quot;
&quot;Yes.&quot;
&quot;Whyzzat?&quot;
&quot;So we can arrest you.&quot;
&quot;So...if I don&#39;t put my gust down, you can&#39;t arrest me?&quot;
Teycanwyn stepped forward, spines raised threateningly. &quot;We&#39;ll do worse than arrest you, you little trib!&quot; he growled, making sure the squall could see both the slapstick and Teycanwyn&#39;s vivid scar which ran from the edge of his spines to his top lip.

To be continued...
